scripts.name: t2cdr
scripts.source:
#!/bin/bash

cd /data/ftpaccess/records
cdr_id=$(cat cdrid)
if ! [ "$cdr_id" -eq "$cdr_id" ] 2>/dev/null
then
    cdr_id=0
    echo $cdr_id > cdrid
fi

for id in $(cat cdrid);
        do 
        for i in $(find -maxdepth 1 -name "*.csv.gz" -type f);
                do
                        id=$((id + 1))
                        if [[ $id -eq 100000 ]]
                        then
                                id=0
                        fi
                mv "$i" "tele2/${i%.csv.gz}-$(printf '%05d' $id).csv.gz";
        done
echo $id > cdrid
echo "Done, last CDR ID is $(printf '%05d' $id)"
done

scripts.name: diameterd-watchdog
scripts.source:
#/bin/bash

######################################################################################################
#
# Description: This file acts as a watchdog for handling the scenarios when the local client
#              is slow-consumer for the subscriber events.
#              PSM on detecting such events, will drop a file and this script will take appropriate
#              actions based on it to restart the respective process/client.
#
######################################################################################################

FILES=/data/psm/restart_diameterd_*

#
# @param1 - The audit string
#
audit() {
    echo -e "[DiameterD watch-dog]: $1" | logger -p local7.notice -t psmd
}

#
# @param1 - The PID of the process to be killed
#
kill_process() {
    local exitCode
    audit "Killing the process PID $1"

    local killOutput
    killOutput=$(kill "$1" 2>&1)
    exitCode=$?

    audit "Killed process with PID - $1. Exit status - $?. Kill output: $killOutput"

    return $exitCode
}

#
# The main function to check for the restart indicator files
#
check_file() {
    for filename in $FILES
    do
        if [ ! -f "$filename" ]
        then
            continue
        fi

        audit "Found file $filename"

        local clientPort
        clientPort=`echo $filename | cut -d'_' -f3`
        audit "Extracted client port - $clientPort"

        local netstatOutput
        netstatOutput=$(netstat -nep 2>/dev/null | grep $clientPort | grep diameterd)
        audit "netstat output: [ $netstatOutput ] "

        local clientPid
        clientPid=`echo $netstatOutput | awk '{print $9}' | cut -d'/' -f1`
        audit "Extracted client pid = $clientPid"

        if [ -z "$clientPid" ] || [ -z "$clientPort" ] || [ ! -n $clientPort ] || [ ! -n $clientPid ]
        then
            audit "Either port($clientPort) or pid($clientPid) is invalid. Removing this invalid file."
            rm -f $filename
            continue
        fi

        kill_process "$clientPid"

        if [ $? -eq 0 ]
        then
            audit "Removing the respective file as process with PID $clientPid has been killed successfully"
            rm -f $filename
        else
            audit "Unable to kill the process with PID - $clientPid. Will be reattempted ..."
        fi
    done
}

# Main invocation
check_file
